3 The night breedes fearefull dreames, which in time of the Pestilence increase terrors. Iob in his affliction crieth out because hee is terrified with the visions of the night;
When I say my couch shall relieue mee, my bed
Iob. 7. 13. 14. 15. shall bring comfort, in my meditation, then fearest thou with dreames, and astonishedst me with visions, my soule choseth rather to be strangled, and to die, then to be in my bones.
